citation.case_name: Public Util. Comm'n of Cal. v. Baltimore Shippers & Receivers Assn., Inc.

html:
389 U.S. 583

88 S.Ct. 694

19 L.Ed.2d 783

PUBLIC UTILITIES COMMISSION OF CALIFORNIA et al.
v.
BALTIMORE SHIPPERS & RECEIVERS ASS'N, INC., et al.

No. 846.

Supreme Court of the United States

October Term, 1967.

January 15, 1968

Mary Moran Pajalich and Bernard A. Peeters, for appellants.

Ronald N. Cobert and Philip R. Ehrenkranz, for appellees Baltimore Shippers & Receivers Ass'n, Inc., and others.

Stanley E. Tobin and Carl M. Gould, for appellees Charles J. Worth Drayage Co. and others.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motions to affirm are granted and the judgment is affirmed.
